The ruler and each lower rank vassal (i.e. the dukes if the ruler is a king) can nominate a successor from among themselves and legitimate children and siblings of the ruler. Dukes are valid electors in both kingdoms and empires. Elective Succession is very popular with the vassals, but they will not approve if their liege personally holds too many elector titles.
